rComments: Lectures poorly organized with no logical transition from one topic to another. There is often repetition, same stuff taught over and over. The textbook is wrote by herself with ambiguous sentences and repetitive content. Definitions of the same thing differs as you go into different chapters. It's nice she created the demand of her book with ESP.

Tip: Even though they warn not to look at past exams, DO go through as many tests as you can well before your exam (while studying) since, although the content may be different the further back you go, the types of questions are mostly the same and often repeated! Also, the TB doesn't have any exam Q., so past tests are your only practice!
